From 93df5e84093d15e6a9788160ce9f39b154897ac5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 6 Aug 2025 11:55:24 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: wifi: mac80211: Continue CAC due to
 punctured channel radar

Currenty, when a radar is detected, mac80211 cancels the CAC timer
(if running) and marks the radar affected sub-channel(s) as unavailable.

Consider a case where we have started radar detection on a DFS channel
with a user configured puncture pattern. If we detect a radar on
the punctured subchannel, we cancel the running CAC timer and mark
the subchannel as unavailable.

We may, however, still continue the radar detection on the DFS
channel. This is valid because the radar is detected on a punctured
subchannel and the punctured channel will not be used for transmission.

Fix this by allowing the CAC timer to continue when a radar is detected
on a punctured subchannel. Make sure to mark / update the state of the
subchannel as unavailable.

Fixes: Ib960576bdd7 ("DFS interference bitmap support during DFS interference detection.")
Patch-work: None
Tag: DFS
Patch-dependency:
subsys/0084-mac80211-radar-bitmap-during-DFS-radar-detection.patch

Signed-off-by: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/util.c | 16 ++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/util.c b/net/mac80211/util.c
index eea5c9d477b6..5a6ddcac9a3d 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/util.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/util.c
@@ -4063,24 +4063,28 @@ ieee80211_dfs_radar_detected_processing(struct ieee80211_local *local,
 	    	    (chandef.chan == radar_channel))
 		    radar_chandef = &ctx->conf.def;
 	}
-	ieee80211_dfs_cac_cancel(local);
-
-	if (radar_chandef)
-		radar_chandef->radar_bitmap = radar_bitmap;
-
-	chandef.radar_bitmap = radar_bitmap;
 
 	if (num_chanctx > 1) {
 		if (local->hw.wiphy->flags & WIPHY_FLAG_SUPPORTS_MLO) {
 			if (WARN_ON(!radar_chandef))
 				return;
 
+			radar_chandef->radar_bitmap = radar_bitmap;
+
+			if (!radar_bitmap || (radar_bitmap & ~radar_chandef->punctured))
+				ieee80211_dfs_cac_cancel(local);
+
 			cfg80211_radar_event(local->hw.wiphy, radar_chandef, GFP_KERNEL);
 		} else {
 			/* XXX: multi-channel is not supported yet */
 			WARN_ON(1);
 		}
 	} else {
+		chandef.radar_bitmap = radar_bitmap;
+
+		if (!radar_bitmap || (radar_bitmap & ~chandef.punctured))
+			ieee80211_dfs_cac_cancel(local);
+
 		cfg80211_radar_event(local->hw.wiphy, &chandef, GFP_KERNEL);
 	}
 }
